The Programming Historian lesson [Facial Recognition in Historical Photographs with Artificial Intelligence in Python](https://programminghistorian.org/en/lessons/facial-recognition-ai-python) introduces key concepts of facial recognition. This tutorial can be expanded to introduce key issues related to inequalities.

**Example: Blackish, Series 5 Episode 10** 
In this episode Diane is “invisible” in her class photo. This can be a starting point to discuss engineered inequity. 

